       <guid isPermaLink="false">https://georgimirchevcom.wordpress.com/?p=9</guid> 
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This post is like a reminder for all Android devs who forgot the fact that the Canvas class has a method &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20191022073334/https://developer.android.com/reference/android/graphics/Canvas#drawArc(android.graphics.RectF,%20float,%20float,%20boolean,%20android.graphics.Paint)&#34;&gt;drawArc&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Or you can use a simple library like: &lt;a href=&#34;https://web.archive.org/web/20191022073334/https://github.com/MarcinMoskala/ArcSeekBar/&#34;&gt;ArcSeekBar&lt;/a&gt;. It has smooth animation, you can control the thumb drawable, progress background and color and many more.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
